HEADWORD: Loathing
<hw>Loath"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Extreme disgust; a feeling of
aversion, nausea, abhorrence, or detestation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The mutual fear and <qex>loathing</qex> of the hostile races.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Loathingly</ent>⟦br⟧
